<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9B0DE5DE113EF935A35751C0A961948260" class="external text" title="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9B0DE5DE113EF935A35751C0A961948260" rel="nofollow">438 Protesters are Arrested at Nevada Nuclear Test Site.</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.globalsecurity.org/wmd/world/france/nuke.htm" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.globalsecurity.org/wmd/world/france/nuke.htm" rel="nofollow">[1]</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> "Chinese Nuclear Tests Allegedly Cause 750,000 Deaths" <i>Epoch Times</i>. March 30, 2009. <a href="http://www.theepochtimes.com/n2/content/view/14535/" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.theepochtimes.com/n2/content/view/14535/" rel="nofollow">[2]</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-Bracken-14"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Bracken_14-0" title="">^</a></b> Paul Bracken, <a href="http://web.mit.edu/ssp/seminars/wed_archives_03fall/bracken.htm" class="external text" title="http://web.mit.edu/ssp/seminars/wed_archives_03fall/bracken.htm" rel="nofollow">The Structure of the Second Nuclear Age</a>, 2003.</li>
<li id="cite_note-15"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://cns.miis.edu/research/safrica/chron.htm" class="external autonumber" title="http://cns.miis.edu/research/safrica/chron.htm" rel="nofollow">[3]</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ww4report.com/node/929" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.ww4report.com/node/929" rel="nofollow">[4]</a>.</li>
